# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# apprendre-francais — example environment file.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (or `.env.local`) and fill in the values.
# Both filenames are git-ignored. The Vite dev/preview server reads them
# automatically and forwards them to the /api/correct middleware.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#   # then edit .env and uncomment the line you want
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# 1) Claude Code OAuth token (RECOMMENDED — uses your Claude Pro/Max
#    subscription quota, no per-token billing).
#
#    How to obtain it on macOS:
#       npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code
#       claude                  # log in once with your Pro/Max account
#       security find-generic-password -s "Claude Code-credentials" -w \
#         | python3 -c "import json,sys;print(json.load(sys.stdin)['claudeAiOauth']['accessToken'])"
#
#    The token starts with sk-ant-oat01-…  (it expires after a while —
#    re-run the command above to refresh it).
#
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=sk-ant-oat01-REPLACE_ME

# 2) Standard Anthropic API key (pay-per-token). Used as a fallback when
#    CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN is not set. Create one at:
#       https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-REPLACE_ME

# 3) Optional — override the Claude model used by the corrector.
#    Defaults to claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929.
#
# CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929
